source_feminine: The ladies imitated the queen: they endeavored to have the Jews considered an inalienable dependence of their fiefs, and to establish the usage that if a Jew domiciled in one barony passed into another, the lady of her former domicil should have the right to seize her possessions.

source_feminine: Insight into how Manning-Sanders believed fairy tales should usually end is given in her foreword to A Book of Witches Now in all these stories, as in fairy tales about witches in general, you may be sure of one thing however terrible the witches may seem – and whatever power they may have to lay spells on people and to work mischief – they are always defeated. ...
translate_feminine: Un aperçu de la façon dont Manning-Sanders pensait que les contes de fées devraient généralement se terminer est donné dans son avant-propos du Livre des Sorcières. Maintenant, dans toutes ces histoires, comme dans les contes de fées sur les sorcières en général, vous pouvez être sûr d'une chose aussi terribles que puissent paraître les sorcières. – et quel que soit le pouvoir dont ils disposent pour jeter des sorts sur les gens et commettre des méfaits – ils sont toujours vaincus. ...

source_feminine: The ritual took place on the Prince's Stone (Slovene Knežji kamen, German Fürstenstein), an ancient Roman column capital near Krnski grad (now Karnburg) and was performed in Slovene by a free peasant who, selected by her peers, in the name of the people of the land questioned the new Princess about her integrity and reminded her of her duties.
